  "body": " An object moving along a horizontal axis has its instantaneous velocity at time in seconds given by the function pictured in Figure , where is measured in feet\/sec. Assume that the curves that make up the parts of the graph of are either portions of straight lines or portions of circles.   The graph of , the velocity function of a moving object.       Determine the exact total distance the object traveled on .    What is the value and meaning of , where is the position function of the moving object?    On which time interval did the object travel the greatest distance: , , or ?    On which time interval(s) is the position function increasing? At which point(s) does achieve a relative maximum?          .     is the change in position of the object on .    On the time interval .     is increasing on the intervals and ; the position function has a relative maximum at .         To find the exact total distance traveled, we need to calculate the area under the velocity function on the interval . This area is the sum of the areas of the triangular region of height and base length on the interval plus the area of the quarter circle of radius on the interval . So the total distance the object traveled on is .    The meaning of is the change in position, or total displacement, of the object on the time interval . Note that was found to be in part (a) and . So, , which means that the object moved 2 feet back toward its original position from time to time .    In part (a) we calculated the distance traveled by the object on the interval to be approximately feet. On the time interval , the object is moving in the opposite direction from the motion on the interval , and the total distance traveled is the area bounds below the -axis on the interval . This area is the sum of the areas of the triangle of height and base length on the interval and the area of the rectangle of height and length on the interval . So the total distance traveled by the object on the interval is . The total distance traveled by the object on the interval is the area bounds above the -axis on the interval . This area is the area of the semicircle of radius on the interval . So the total distance traveled by the object on the interval is . Thus, the object traveled the greatest distance on the time interval .    We know that the position function is increasing when the velocity is positive, so is increasing on the intervals and . Since is positive to the left of and then negative to the right of , the position function is increasing to the left of then decreasing to the right of . Thus, the position function has a relative maximum point at . There are no other points with this property, so this is the only relative maximum value of on this interval. We also can note that increases from to , culminating in a local maximum value at .     "
